  "texts": [
    "We intend this to mean: if x ′ ⊑ x, f i (x ′)↓, and f i (x ′) ≬ z, then f i (x)↓ and f i (x) ≬ z, but we leave the definedness implicit.",
    "In Holliday 2014, this condition was called f -refinability.",
    "In Holliday 2014, this condition was called f -persistence.",
    "Of course, we are treating all of these as classes of posets, rather than algebraic structures of particular similarity types.",
    "This also holds for extended quasi-functional principal frames (seeDefinitions 4.19, 4.25, and 4.36), for which f i (⊥) = ⊥."
